* On your console, go to remove your profile, do a cold boot and and then re-install your profile.

* Restore your console to the factory default settings.

1. Go to the Home screen. Press the Menu button on the Wireless Controller.
2. Select Settings > System > Restore factory defaults.
3. Select “Yes” on Read the warning message screen.

Note: Doing a restore factory defaults will delete your saved games, but the achievements are unlocking (it doesn’t unlock past achievements) and the profile picture is also back.
